      "content": "Yes, the placement of the rebar is absolutely critical, as it must be positioned precisely where the tensile stresses are expected to be highest. If the reinforcement is placed incorrectly, the load will be borne by the weaker concrete in tension, leading to premature failure. Engineers use detailed structural calculations, stress diagrams, and design codes to determine the exact depth and spacing of the steel. This ensures that the steel is strategically located to counteract the anticipated internal forces throughout the entire cross-section.",
